headline: ON Semiconductor Stock Rises. The Chip Maker’s Worst Days Are Behind It, CEO Says.
summary: ON Semiconductor  was on track to notch its third straight day of gains Wednesday after the chip maker’s CEO stressed that things would only improve following a mixed first-quarter print.  Shares climbed 5.8% to $50.11 on Wednesday, on pace for their best three-day stretch since November 2021, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  ON Semiconductor  jumped 11% Tuesday after CEO Hassane El-Khoury appeared at the Bank of America Global Technology Conference and repeatedly emphasized that On Semi was “expecting growth.”
